This function `mask_pii` processes a given text to mask potential Personally Identifiable Information (PII) such as emails, US phone numbers, Social Security Numbers (SSNs), and 16-digit credit card numbers. Each type of PII is replaced with a stable placeholder, preserving the surrounding context. The function uses regular expressions to identify and replace these patterns.
